</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1758,2035]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,151,645]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1758,1783]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
(Based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Manter, H. W." box="[405,554,1759,1783]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="257 - 416" refId="ref34716" refString="Manter, H. W. (1947) The digenetic trematodes of marine fishes of Tortugas, Florida. American Midland Naturalist, 38, 257 - 416. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2421571" type="journal article" year="1947">Manter 1947</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Yamaguti, S." box="[567,743,1758,1783]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref35883" refString="Yamaguti, S. (1958) Systema Helminthum. Vol 1. The digenetic trematodes of vertebrates. Part 1. Interscience Publishers, New York, 979 pp." type="book" year="1958">Yamaguti 1958</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cribb, T. H." box="[756,887,1758,1783]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="621 - 639" refId="ref33192" refString="Cribb, T. H. (2005) Family Apocreadiidae Skrjabin, 1942. In: Jones, A., Bray, R. A. &amp; Gibson, D. I. (Eds.), Keys to the Trematoda. Vol. 2. CABI Publishing and the Natural History Museum, Wallingford, pp. 621 - 639." type="book chapter" year="2005">Cribb 2005</bibRefCitation>
) Body small, rounded, oval-elongate. Tegument spinous. Eye-spot pigment present as granules in forebody. Oral sucker subterminal, unspecialized. Ventral sucker unspecialized, pre-equatorial. Prepharynx very short. Pharynx large. Esophagus short, muscular. Intestinal bifurcation in forebody. Caeca wide, end blindly, extend well into post-equatorial region. Testes two, tandem, postovarian, in hindbody. Cirrus pouch absent. Seminal vesicle tubular. Pars prostatica present. Genital pore median, immediately posterior to ventral sucker. Ovary globular, smooth, in hindbody, median to submedian, pre-testicular. Canalicular seminal receptacle and Mehlis’ gland present. Laurer’s canal present. Vitellarium follicular; follicles lateral, mainly in hindbody and just enter forebody. Uterus between ovary and ventral sucker. Eggs medium in size, thin-shelled. Excretory vesicle I-shaped, extend to level of pharynx; excretory pore terminal. Adults in intestine of marine serranid fishes; Atlantic and Pacific Oceans.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1281,223,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,645]" box="[199,1281,223,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,450,223,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<typeStatus box="[199,258,223,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Type</typeStatus>
and only genus.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Manter, 1949" authorityName="Manter" authorityYear="1949" box="[457,728,224,248]" class="Trematoda" family="Apocreadiidae" genus="Postporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[457,571,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Postporus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Manter, H. W." box="[578,728,224,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="432 - 435" refId="ref34756" refString="Manter, H. W. (1949) An additional trematode from Tortugas, Florida, and a new name for Opisthoporus Manter, 1947, preoccupied. American Midland Naturalist, 41, 432 - 435. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2421722" type="journal article" year="1949">Manter, 1949</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(Syn. 
<taxonomicName authority="Manter, 1947" authorityName="Manter" authorityYear="1947" box="[801,1111,223,248]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cyclophoridae" genus="Opisthoporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[801,953,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Opisthoporus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Manter, H. W." box="[961,1111,224,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="257 - 416" refId="ref34716" refString="Manter, H. W. (1947) The digenetic trematodes of marine fishes of Tortugas, Florida. American Midland Naturalist, 38, 257 - 416. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2421571" type="journal article" year="1947">Manter, 1947</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
pre-occupied).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,260,285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Remarks.</emphasis>
Members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yamaguti" authorityYear="1958" box="[515,647,260,285]" class="Trematoda" family="Apocreadiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Postporinae">Postporinae</taxonomicName>
are unique within the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Manter" authorityYear="1934" box="[910,1056,260,285]" class="Trematoda" family="Megaperidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="family">Megaperidae</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1065,1169,260,285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">n. comb.</emphasis>
in possessing a genital pore that is median and immediately posterior to the ventral sucker. At present, this is a monotypic subfamily with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Manter" authorityYear="1949" box="[151,265,333,356]" class="Trematoda" family="Apocreadiidae" genus="Postporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,265,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Postporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[343,391,333,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">type</typeStatus>
and only genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Cribb, T. H." box="[582,716,332,357]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="621 - 639" refId="ref33192" refString="Cribb, T. H. (2005) Family Apocreadiidae Skrjabin, 1942. In: Jones, A., Bray, R. A. &amp; Gibson, D. I. (Eds.), Keys to the Trematoda. Vol. 2. CABI Publishing and the Natural History Museum, Wallingford, pp. 621 - 639." type="book chapter" year="2005">Cribb 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<bibRefCitation author="Manter, H. W." box="[199,364,368,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="257 - 416" refId="ref34716" refString="Manter, H. W. (1947) The digenetic trematodes of marine fishes of Tortugas, Florida. American Midland Naturalist, 38, 257 - 416. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2421571" type="journal article" year="1947">Manter (1947)</bibRefCitation>
erected 
<taxonomicName authority="Manter, 1947" authorityName="Manter" authorityYear="1947" box="[465,780,367,392]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cyclophoridae" genus="Opisthoporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[465,617,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Opisthoporus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Manter, H. W." box="[627,780,368,392]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="257 - 416" refId="ref34716" refString="Manter, H. W. (1947) The digenetic trematodes of marine fishes of Tortugas, Florida. American Midland Naturalist, 38, 257 - 416. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2421571" type="journal article" year="1947">Manter, 1947</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with the description of 
<taxonomicName authority="Manter, 1947" authorityName="Manter" authorityYear="1947" class="Gastropoda" family="Cyclophoridae" genus="Opisthoporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="epinepheli">
<emphasis box="[1060,1340,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Opisthoporus epinepheli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Manter, H. W." pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="257 - 416" refId="ref34716" refString="Manter, H. W. (1947) The digenetic trematodes of marine fishes of Tortugas, Florida. American Midland Naturalist, 38, 257 - 416. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2421571" type="journal article" year="1947">Manter, 1947</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
parasitizing the intestine of the red grouper, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Valenciennes)" baseAuthorityName="Valenciennes" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[794,1204,404,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Epinephelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="morio">
<emphasis box="[794,1017,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Epinephelus morio</emphasis>
(Valenciennes)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Manter, 1947" authorityName="Manter" authorityYear="1947" class="Gastropoda" family="Cyclophoridae" genus="Opisthoporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mycteropercae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Opisthoporus mycteropercae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Manter, H. W." box="[324,476,440,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="257 - 416" refId="ref34716" refString="Manter, H. W. (1947) The digenetic trematodes of marine fishes of Tortugas, Florida. American Midland Naturalist, 38, 257 - 416. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2421571" type="journal article" year="1947">Manter, 1947</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
infecting the intestine of the yellowfin grouper, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1037,1436,439,464]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" genus="Mycteroperca" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="venenosa">
<emphasis box="[1037,1305,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Mycteroperca venenosa</emphasis>
(Linnaeus)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[158,300,476,501]" class="Actinopterygii" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="order">Perciformes</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Swainson" authorityYear="1839" box="[314,438,476,501]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serranidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Serranidae</taxonomicName>
), from off Dry 
<collectingCountry box="[625,726,477,501]" name="Haiti" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Tortugas</collectingCountry>
, Florida. This digenean genus was renamed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Manter" authorityYear="1949" box="[1251,1365,477,500]" class="Trematoda" family="Apocreadiidae" genus="Postporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1251,1365,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Postporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
when 
<bibRefCitation author="Manter, H. W." box="[151,313,512,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="432 - 435" refId="ref34756" refString="Manter, H. W. (1949) An additional trematode from Tortugas, Florida, and a new name for Opisthoporus Manter, 1947, preoccupied. American Midland Naturalist, 41, 432 - 435. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2421722" type="journal article" year="1949">Manter (1949)</bibRefCitation>
discovered that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Manter" authorityYear="1947" box="[496,648,511,536]" class="Gastropoda" family="Cyclophoridae" genus="Opisthoporus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[496,648,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Opisthoporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was pre-occupied, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Cribb, T. H. &amp; Gibson, D. I." box="[911,1186,511,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refId="ref33441" refString="Cribb, T. H. &amp; Gibson, D. I. (2017 b) Postporus Manter, 1949. World Register of Marine Species (WoRMS). Available from: http: // www. marinespecies. org / aphia. php? p = taxdetails &amp; id = 415856 (accessed 6 September 2017)" type="url" year="2017">Cribb &amp; Gibson (2017b)</bibRefCitation>
have since designated 
<taxonomicName authority="(Manter, 1947) Manter 1949 a" authorityName="Manter" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Manter" baseAuthorityYear="1947" box="[151,784,548,572]" class="Trematoda" family="Apocreadiidae" genus="Postporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="mycteropercae">
<emphasis box="[151,436,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Postporus mycteropercae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Manter, H. W." box="[451,605,548,572]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="257 - 416" refId="ref34716" refString="Manter, H. W. (1947) The digenetic trematodes of marine fishes of Tortugas, Florida. American Midland Naturalist, 38, 257 - 416. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2421571" type="journal article" year="1947">Manter, 1947</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Manter, H. W." box="[620,764,548,572]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="432 - 435" refId="ref34756" refString="Manter, H. W. (1949) An additional trematode from Tortugas, Florida, and a new name for Opisthoporus Manter, 1947, preoccupied. American Midland Naturalist, 41, 432 - 435. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2421722" type="journal article" year="1949">Manter 1949</bibRefCitation>
a
</taxonomicName>
synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Manter, 1947) Manter 1949" authorityName="Manter" authorityYear="1949" baseAuthorityName="Manter" baseAuthorityYear="1947" class="Trematoda" family="Apocreadiidae" genus="Postporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="epinepheli">
<emphasis box="[933,1171,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Postporus epinepheli</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Manter, H. W." box="[1186,1339,548,572]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="257 - 416" refId="ref34716" refString="Manter, H. W. (1947) The digenetic trematodes of marine fishes of Tortugas, Florida. American Midland Naturalist, 38, 257 - 416. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2421571" type="journal article" year="1947">Manter, 1947</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Manter, H. W." pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="432 - 435" refId="ref34756" refString="Manter, H. W. (1949) An additional trematode from Tortugas, Florida, and a new name for Opisthoporus Manter, 1947, preoccupied. American Midland Naturalist, 41, 432 - 435. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 2421722" type="journal article" year="1949">Manter 1949</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[270,318,584,608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">type</typeStatus>
and only species known of this genus. As alluded to by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cribb, T. H." box="[999,1142,583,608]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="621 - 639" refId="ref33192" refString="Cribb, T. H. (2005) Family Apocreadiidae Skrjabin, 1942. In: Jones, A., Bray, R. A. &amp; Gibson, D. I. (Eds.), Keys to the Trematoda. Vol. 2. CABI Publishing and the Natural History Museum, Wallingford, pp. 621 - 639." type="book chapter" year="2005">Cribb (2005</bibRefCitation>
, p. 624), the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yamaguti" authorityYear="1958" box="[1304,1436,583,608]" class="Trematoda" family="Apocreadiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plagiorchiida" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Postporinae">Postporinae</taxonomicName>
remains highly dubious and needs further (especially molecular) study.
</paragraph>
